<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fontelas &amp; R. Romero" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia gracilis" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Microlicia gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted extent of occurrence (EOO = 10 km2) and area of occupancy (AOO = 8 km2) and, according to the IUCN Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" publicationUrl="https://iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuideLines.pdf" refId="B32" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. https://iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuideLines.pdf" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14." url="https://iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuideLines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
), is preliminarily assessed as Critically Endangered [CR B1ab (iii) + 2ab (iii)]. So far, collections of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. gracilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">M. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been made only outside the boundaries of the Chapada dos Veadeiros National Park and, therefore, it is not protected by any conservation units. The restricted distribution of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. gracilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">M. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also contributes to its degree of threat, since its populations are exposed to frequent burning caused by farmers, in addition to the expansion of agricultural borders in the region (
<bibRefCitation author="Felfili, JM" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B8" refString="Felfili, JM, Rezende, AV, Silva-Junior, MC, 2007. Biogeografia do Bioma Cerrado: Vegetacao e Solos da Chapada dos Veadeiros. Brasilia: Universidade de Brasilia/Finatec, 256 pp." title="Biogeografia do Bioma Cerrado: Vegetacao e Solos da Chapada dos Veadeiros. Brasilia: Universidade de Brasilia / Finatec, 256 pp." year="2007">Felfili et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alves, MM" journalOrPublisher="Enciclopedia Biosfera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="752 - 768" refId="B2" refString="Alves, MM, Matricardi, EAT, Pereira, RS, 2013. Dinamica espaco-temporal do fogo entre 1999 a 2009 no Parque Nacional da Chapada dos Veadeiros. Enciclopedia Biosfera 9 (1): 752 - 768" title="Dinamica espaco-temporal do fogo entre 1999 a 2009 no Parque Nacional da Chapada dos Veadeiros." volume="9" year="2013">Alves et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Flowers have been collected in March, May and June and fruits in May and June.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
The specific epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="gracilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="gracilis">gracilis</taxonomicName>
&quot; refers to the very delicate and fragile branches and leaves and the small size of the flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
